WEBVTT

00:00:00.560 --> 00:00:11.560
Welcome to another edition of JW Broadcasting. Thank you for joining us. You will

00:00:11.560 --> 00:00:17.480
be delighted to see reports of some of the many exciting activities that have

00:00:17.480 --> 00:00:24.079
taken place this past calendar year in furthering Kingdom Interest. You will

00:00:24.079 --> 00:00:31.320
also hear experiences from construction projects in Micronesia that the

00:00:31.320 --> 00:00:38.439
brothers involved attribute to Jehovah's Intervention. And have you benefited

00:00:38.439 --> 00:00:45.320
from the translation of JW Broadcasting into languages other than English? We

00:00:45.320 --> 00:00:52.359
will take you behind the scenes to see how the program is made available to as

00:00:52.359 --> 00:01:02.679
many of God's sheep as possible. This is the January program of JW Broadcasting.

00:01:02.679 --> 00:01:26.290
Our theme for this month's broadcast is sincere

00:01:26.290 --> 00:01:34.489
commendation is always appropriate. One definition of commendation is the

00:01:34.489 --> 00:01:41.170
act of praising or approving of someone. And when it is given in a sincere,

00:01:41.170 --> 00:01:49.049
genuine way, how encouraging it can be to the one receiving it. That makes us

00:01:49.049 --> 00:01:57.730
think of Proverbs 15 23, which says, a word spoken at the right time, how good it

00:01:57.730 --> 00:02:06.609
is. Similarly, Proverbs 12 25 talks about how anxiety can weigh a person's heart

00:02:06.609 --> 00:02:15.610
down, but then says, but a good word cheers it up. A 19th century author

00:02:15.610 --> 00:02:24.090
gested, I can live for two months on a good compliment. But now, keeping our

00:02:24.090 --> 00:02:30.889
theme in mind, let us talk about Jehovah and Jesus. Can you imagine how much

00:02:30.889 --> 00:02:36.889
Jehovah must have appreciated his only begotten son whom we have come to know

00:02:36.889 --> 00:02:46.050
is Jesus? Jesus had faithfully supported his father for eons of time. But then

00:02:46.050 --> 00:02:51.289
when he learned of Jehovah's purpose to buy back the hope of everlasting life

00:02:51.289 --> 00:02:59.289
for imperfect humans, what did Jesus do? Did he make excuses? As to why he could

00:02:59.289 --> 00:03:07.090
not leave heaven and come to the earth? Father, I have many projects going on and I

00:03:07.090 --> 00:03:13.969
have my friends here in heaven. And besides, I would miss being with you. I just

00:03:13.969 --> 00:03:19.129
don't have the right circumstances. Furthermore, this will be a very difficult

00:03:19.129 --> 00:03:29.050
painful humiliating assignment. It seems like this is a good assignment for Gabriel.

00:03:29.050 --> 00:03:37.849
No, Jesus did not even slightly reason this way. He willingly made sacrifices that

00:03:37.849 --> 00:03:46.569
cost him dearly. He changed life forms, going from a majestic spirit creature to a

00:03:46.569 --> 00:03:55.330
little baby completely dependent on his parents. Later, as a perfect child, he

00:03:55.330 --> 00:04:03.169
remained fully in subjection to imperfect parents. Then, as an adult, he worked

00:04:03.169 --> 00:04:10.889
his heart out in starting a preaching campaign that continues to this very day.

00:04:10.889 --> 00:04:16.250
You wonder how many pairs of sandals he may have worn out during his three and a

00:04:16.250 --> 00:04:25.250
half year ministry. Then, he died an agonizing death on a torture stake in order to

00:04:25.250 --> 00:04:33.370
provide a corresponding ransom according to Jehovah's purpose. He contributed his

00:04:33.370 --> 00:04:41.209
very life to support the work that Jehovah wanted accomplished at that time.

00:04:41.930 --> 00:04:48.889
Undoubtedly, you recall the video that was shown during the final talk of last year's

00:04:48.889 --> 00:04:57.129
regional convention. It helped us better appreciate what Jesus did for us. By his

00:04:57.129 --> 00:05:04.810
selfless act, he opened the way for everlasting life, whether in heaven or on earth.

00:05:05.769 --> 00:05:13.529
But now the question is, did Jehovah appreciate all that his son did to support him,

00:05:13.529 --> 00:05:22.250
sanctifying his name, and vindicating his sovereignty? Absolutely. We know he did.

00:05:22.250 --> 00:05:33.370
Imagine Jesus waste deep in the Jordan River. His hair still dripping from his baptism. He looks

00:05:34.329 --> 00:05:43.209
up and in some way sees the heavens open up and God's spirit descend like a dove and come upon

00:05:43.209 --> 00:05:53.850
him. Then he hears Jehovah's own voice from heaven say, this is my son, the beloved whom I have

00:05:54.329 --> 00:06:03.529
approved. If we think about it, Jehovah packed a lot of commendation into that one sentence.

00:06:04.649 --> 00:06:12.089
This is my son. Jehovah, in effect, was saying, son, I am proud to be your father.

00:06:13.370 --> 00:06:23.209
The beloved Jehovah was saying, I love you son, whom I have approved. Jehovah was saying,

00:06:24.009 --> 00:06:31.930
I am very happy son with what you have done thus far. And I know I'm going to be very happy

00:06:31.930 --> 00:06:40.410
with what you will yet do. Can you imagine how good all of that commendation made Jesus feel?

00:06:42.170 --> 00:06:50.089
Yes, Jehovah appreciated all of the sacrifices Jesus had made to support what he wanted accomplished

00:06:50.730 --> 00:07:01.180
and he expressed his appreciation. Jesus, being the exact reflection of his father,

00:07:02.139 --> 00:07:10.939
was also a perfect example of one who commended others. As recorded at Luke 22, 28, and 29,

00:07:11.740 --> 00:07:18.300
do you remember what Jesus said to his faithful 11 apostles on the last night of his life as a human?

00:07:18.379 --> 00:07:29.899
You are the ones who have stuck with me in my trials. And I make a covenant with you for a kingdom.

00:07:31.740 --> 00:07:41.500
Warm commendation indeed. Consider another example. Although Jesus provided constructive

00:07:41.500 --> 00:07:50.060
counsel to several congregations, he also warmly commended them. Notice what he said to the

00:07:50.060 --> 00:08:03.740
congregation in Thyatira at Revelation 2 verse 19. In verse 19, Jesus said, I know your deeds

00:08:04.699 --> 00:08:13.420
and your love and faith and ministry and endurance and that your deeds of late are more than those

00:08:14.139 --> 00:08:24.220
you did at first. Such detailed, thoughtful commendation likely move the congregation to continue

00:08:24.220 --> 00:08:33.320
making similar progress thereafter. Well now we have talked about the two best examples in the

00:08:33.320 --> 00:08:44.519
universe of ones who are generous with commendation, Jehovah and Jesus. But now what about us?

00:08:45.720 --> 00:08:55.879
Ephesians 5, 1 urges us to become imitators of God. And our convention theme this past year

00:08:55.960 --> 00:09:06.279
was imitate Jesus. And this counsel also applies to the governing body. The governing body would like

00:09:06.279 --> 00:09:16.360
to follow Jehovah's and Jesus good example by providing warm commendation to you, dear brothers and

00:09:16.360 --> 00:09:24.600
sisters. So many of you are so responsive to any suggestions or appeals made to you

00:09:25.559 --> 00:09:35.960
by the faithful and discreet slave. In the late 2015 monthly program, we shared our interest in

00:09:36.679 --> 00:09:45.080
expediting the construction of new kingdom halls and remote translation offices. And we explained

00:09:45.080 --> 00:09:53.960
some of the financial challenges we were facing in being able to do so. We discerned that contributions

00:09:53.960 --> 00:10:04.919
immediately went up by more than 15% for the months of June and July. We thank you very much.

00:10:07.240 --> 00:10:13.320
Not only are older ones in Jehovah's organization responding with generosity,

00:10:14.360 --> 00:10:20.039
the governing body has been deeply touched by the response of many young ones.

00:10:21.000 --> 00:10:28.919
It's just one example. I personally received a precious letter, Dear Brother Lat.

00:10:30.200 --> 00:10:39.799
Hello, I am 13 years old. The reason I wrote this letter is because of the May JW Broadcasting.

00:10:40.759 --> 00:10:48.200
I was motivated to contribute to the worldwide work. I have been saving up

00:10:49.159 --> 00:10:57.240
and my relatives gave me some money. I hope it helps. I also want to thank you and the other

00:10:57.240 --> 00:11:07.559
governing body members for the Korean JW Broadcasting. Now, my whole family can understand much more

00:11:07.559 --> 00:11:15.559
and benefit from it. My whole family wants to appreciate all of this. Please tell the other

00:11:15.559 --> 00:11:24.360
governing body members also. And then she drew a smiley face. So because you motivated me in

00:11:24.360 --> 00:11:33.960
financial ways, I was also motivated in spiritual ways. I am doing auxiliary pioneering during summer

00:11:34.039 --> 00:11:44.600
break. One more time. My family and I want to say thank you. And then she drew a big red heart

00:11:45.159 --> 00:11:51.559
at the end of her letter. Well, I sent the check to the Treasurer's office, but I'm definitely

00:11:51.559 --> 00:12:03.179
keeping her touching letter and her adorable picture. Comments such as these have moved us to

00:12:03.179 --> 00:12:12.059
want to use this January 2016 broadcast program to thank you from the bottom of our hearts

00:12:12.860 --> 00:12:22.220
for your support and also to update you on what has happened since last May. So many good things

00:12:22.220 --> 00:12:33.860
are happening. So we ask what has been accomplished in the past eight months? Well, we continue to finance

00:12:34.899 --> 00:12:41.700
the weekly costs to feed and house the more than 25,000 Bethel family members worldwide

00:12:42.659 --> 00:12:50.179
and to help support over 55,000 others in special full-time service. We have been able to continue

00:12:50.179 --> 00:12:58.820
to fund the huge construction project of building the World Headquarters Facility in Warwick,

00:12:58.820 --> 00:13:07.139
New York. Additionally, large branch construction and renovation projects that were underway

00:13:08.419 --> 00:13:15.779
are being supported. And around the world, considerable audio and video equipment has been

00:13:15.779 --> 00:13:25.860
purchased to show the entire program of our imitate Jesus Convention on big screens or monitors.

00:13:26.659 --> 00:13:35.539
Seeing the participants up close holds our attention and enhances the learning experience.

00:13:37.220 --> 00:13:45.860
You may not realize it, but there were 52 videos and almost 30 other audio and visual aids presented

00:13:45.860 --> 00:13:53.860
during this convention, making a total of some 80 presentations for our enjoyment.

00:13:54.580 --> 00:14:03.379
In addition to all of the foregoing, in the past eight months, over 2,000 kingdom halls have been built

00:14:04.259 --> 00:14:12.980
or are in the process of being completed. That average is more than eight kingdom halls being built

00:14:13.620 --> 00:14:23.299
every day, which is truly amazing. Also, over 50 remote translation office facilities have been

00:14:23.299 --> 00:14:33.620
completed or are now in the process of being built. Does all of this mean, though, that we have

00:14:33.620 --> 00:14:41.779
accomplished all of our goals? You remember that in our May program, we mentioned the willing

00:14:41.779 --> 00:14:49.700
generosity of the Israelites in the wilderness when they were asked to contribute to the fabrication

00:14:49.779 --> 00:14:59.139
and construction of the tabernacle for true worship. You recall that in Exodus 35, it says that

00:14:59.139 --> 00:15:07.940
everyone whose heart impelled Him and everyone whose spirit incited Him came and brought their

00:15:07.940 --> 00:15:17.220
contribution for Jehovah. And in chapter 36 verse 7, it says, the goods were enough for all the work

00:15:17.220 --> 00:15:30.330
to be done and more than enough. So we ask, were the Israelites more appreciative and responsive

00:15:30.330 --> 00:15:40.490
than we are today? No. As we said earlier, you are to be commended for your immediate generous

00:15:40.490 --> 00:15:48.090
response to the May broadcast. You responded similar to the Israelites in Moses time.

00:15:48.490 --> 00:15:59.210
The difference, however, between the Israelites giving an ours today is that they only had one project

00:15:59.210 --> 00:16:08.730
to construct. When it was completed, that was all it was needed. However, as you know, we have

00:16:08.730 --> 00:16:17.289
thousands of projects that need our continued support. It is not just a two month undertaking.

00:16:18.490 --> 00:16:25.850
In fact, as announced at the annual meeting this past October, the governing body is so serious

00:16:25.850 --> 00:16:33.129
about advancing kingdom interest in the field that we have re-analyzed ways. We can cut back

00:16:34.090 --> 00:16:44.809
at all the branches so as to redirect more funds to the field. For example, many long standing

00:16:44.809 --> 00:16:55.049
Bethel routines and services are being reduced or eliminated. This will result in fewer members

00:16:55.049 --> 00:17:05.049
of the Bethel family being required. The governing body is absolutely confident, completely confident

00:17:05.769 --> 00:17:14.170
that this initiative and other cost-saving initiatives that we're taking coupled with your

00:17:14.170 --> 00:17:23.289
continued support will enable us to care for all the needs in the field. On behalf of the governing

00:17:23.289 --> 00:17:33.849
body, I would like to borrow the inspired words of 2 Thessalonians, chapter 1, verses 3 and 4.

00:17:33.930 --> 00:17:39.930
We express the words of Paul to you, dear brothers and sisters.

00:17:41.930 --> 00:17:53.049
We are obligated always to give thanks to God for you, brothers. This is fitting because your

00:17:53.049 --> 00:17:59.769
faith is growing exceedingly and the love of each and every one of you is increasing toward one

00:17:59.769 --> 00:18:09.529
another. As a result, we ourselves take pride in you among the congregations of God because of

00:18:09.529 --> 00:18:23.509
your endurance and faith. Again, we sincerely thank you for your generous support of Jehovah's

00:18:23.509 --> 00:18:33.829
Great Work in these exciting last days. But now, during this broadcast, we would like to show you

00:18:33.829 --> 00:18:46.220
some of the things being accomplished as a result of your generosity. This past summer, it was my

00:18:46.220 --> 00:18:55.180
privilege to attend a large regional convention in Stockholm, Sweden. Brothers and sisters from Sweden,

00:18:55.180 --> 00:19:01.740
Denmark, Norway, Iceland, Greenland, the Faroe Islands, and also the Swedish Circuit in Finland

00:19:02.859 --> 00:19:10.460
were present at this historic convention. While this event was a great spiritual boost for the

00:19:10.460 --> 00:19:18.619
witnesses, some of you may know that the majority of the local residents do not believe in God.

00:19:19.579 --> 00:19:30.059
Many consider themselves atheists, but the conduct and professionalism of Jehovah's people made our

00:19:30.059 --> 00:19:51.609
great impact. First, the branch offices were merged. And the result was a new branch office, Scandinavia

00:19:51.609 --> 00:20:00.250
branch. We thought that if all the brothers in Scandinavia should benefit from this unity, then we

00:20:00.250 --> 00:20:09.960
had to have a convention in Stockholm. Here, we were allowed to arrange a regional convention,

00:20:09.960 --> 00:20:17.640
but one of enormous size. Having 50,000 brothers gathered together for three days is the largest

00:20:17.640 --> 00:20:25.640
bureaucratic event ever in Scandinavia. So, we began to look for a facility and we found friends

00:20:25.640 --> 00:20:40.490
Arena. I think we have had a very good collaboration. Many times, I have thought, wow,

00:20:40.569 --> 00:20:45.529
these people working for you as the organizers of infrastructure, logistics, and so on,

00:20:45.529 --> 00:20:54.519
we should work with them more often. The use of technology has been the greatest challenge.

00:20:54.519 --> 00:20:58.440
Obviously, with such a last project, many details have to come together.

00:20:59.960 --> 00:21:04.200
There are four languages and three sign languages, and all this have to be tied together and

00:21:04.200 --> 00:21:11.240
work at the same time. It has been a challenge, but we made it work. All the experts argued that it

00:21:11.240 --> 00:21:51.049
would be impossible to have four languages at one arena. In the morning, families with children

00:21:51.049 --> 00:21:59.609
and strollers arrived. Some elderly publishers get up at 5.30 or 6 a.m., getting on the bus to be

00:21:59.609 --> 00:22:06.569
