00:34:47.380 --> 00:34:56.099
My name is Travis Brooks. My wife Lacey and I serve in Micronesia. Our assignment is serving in

00:34:56.099 --> 00:35:02.179
the LDC department, which is the local design construction department. We care for all the islands

00:35:02.179 --> 00:35:08.099
of Micronesia. It covers the same distance from California to New York, but if you took all those

00:35:08.099 --> 00:35:13.460
islands and put them together, it would be smaller than the state of Rhode Island. So it's very vast

00:35:13.460 --> 00:35:22.579
and spread out. We've seen Jehovah's hand many times throughout the years on our projects.

00:35:23.619 --> 00:35:30.820
One that stands out to us is the RIREP congregation in particular. This congregation had been

00:35:30.820 --> 00:35:37.059
meeting in a house for a number of years, and they'd have 70, 80, 90, and attendance at times,

00:35:37.780 --> 00:35:41.619
but they would sit outside because they couldn't fit in the house, and many of them would

00:35:41.619 --> 00:35:46.980
listen through the window or observe through the door. It would rain and they'd have a tarp set up

00:35:46.980 --> 00:35:53.219
just to try to keep dry. So we found this piece of property, but the problem was that the government

00:35:53.219 --> 00:35:59.380
had just placed a ban on dredging sand and coral out of the ocean or off the beaches. Without

00:35:59.380 --> 00:36:05.059
having that, we wouldn't be able to mix our concrete to accomplish our project. So there was one

00:36:05.059 --> 00:36:11.219
company on the island that had stockpiled sand and aggregate. We had gone to them a number of

00:36:11.219 --> 00:36:17.780
times telling them, asking them if we could purchase just eight yards of cement for our

00:36:17.780 --> 00:36:24.739
footings so that we could at least get started, and they kept denying our request and the construction

00:36:24.739 --> 00:36:31.780
overseer and myself decided we'd go one more time to that cement company and plead our case with

00:36:31.780 --> 00:36:39.619
them. When we pulled into the parking lot of the company and discussed maybe what we could say

00:36:40.579 --> 00:36:45.780
to convince them to at least sell us the eight yards that we needed. We made it a matter of

00:36:45.780 --> 00:36:52.820
prayer again, and we both exited the vehicle, and as we were approaching the doors of the company,

00:36:53.539 --> 00:36:59.380
this blue pickup pulled in and kind of intercepted us. The gentleman, local man, hopped out of his

00:36:59.380 --> 00:37:07.539
truck and said, can I help you? And he was the man who was in charge. Well, we explained our situation,

00:37:07.539 --> 00:37:12.340
and he said, well, you'll have your concrete the next morning. It was interesting about that,

00:37:12.340 --> 00:37:19.059
and which really made us feel like Jehovah had a hand in the matter, was that gentleman had just

00:37:19.059 --> 00:37:24.820
flown in the night before from another island. He had been gone for quite some time. He had

00:37:24.820 --> 00:37:32.420
pulled in, talked to us, and then hop back in his truck and drove away. So we wondered why did he

00:37:32.500 --> 00:37:38.500
pull in in the first place? Well, we didn't want to argue with it, and we just took advantage of

00:37:38.500 --> 00:37:43.539
the situation, and the next morning, seven o'clock, the truck rolled in, and we poured our footings.

00:37:45.219 --> 00:37:50.179
So we kept moving forward with the project, so we got to that stage where we would need to fill

00:37:50.179 --> 00:37:58.099
the blockwork with 80 yards of sand on an island with no sand. So again, we made it a matter of

00:37:58.179 --> 00:38:04.820
prayer, and knew that if, again, Jehovah wanted to build, it would be built. So we scoured the island

00:38:04.820 --> 00:38:11.139
again to see if there was anybody willing, and we were unsuccessful. So on our way back to the

00:38:12.019 --> 00:38:18.739
construction site, and the construction overseer, and I stopped at a store to purchase something,

00:38:18.739 --> 00:38:22.739
and we were talking to the gentleman behind the counter, explaining the situation to him,

00:38:22.739 --> 00:38:28.739
and the man asked, well, how much sand do you need? And we told him, oh, 80 yards is quite a bit,

00:38:29.380 --> 00:38:34.500
and the man said, well, I have 90 yards in my backyard. I don't have anything to do with it,

00:38:34.500 --> 00:38:39.300
so you're more than welcome to it. He said, when do you need it? He said, well, we need it

00:38:39.300 --> 00:38:45.219
more morning. And the man said, well, I have a dump truck too, so I'll see you in the morning.

00:38:45.219 --> 00:38:49.460
All the next morning, he showed up, and we were able to fill that area and move on with the project.

00:38:51.860 --> 00:38:58.500
Another experience that really stands out to me is an experience we had on the island of Yap.

00:38:58.500 --> 00:39:04.260
