00:39:04.260 --> 00:39:08.019
Kingdom Hall because of the growth that they've had in the congregation. They've outgrown their

00:39:08.019 --> 00:39:16.179
Kingdom Hall. So for that extension, we would need cement and sand for backfill. And again,

00:39:16.179 --> 00:39:21.300
this was an island which is ironic that you can't really get sand on because there's

00:39:21.300 --> 00:39:27.380
no companies that sell it. So what you do is you go from village to village asking the village chief

00:39:28.019 --> 00:39:34.099
if he would be willing to sell sand off of his beach. Well, after visiting all the villages,

00:39:34.820 --> 00:39:40.579
no one was willing to sell any of their sand that we needed. And so we reached the last village

00:39:40.579 --> 00:39:46.980
which was willing to sell the sand. But the problem was there was a dispute between two chiefs

00:39:46.980 --> 00:39:51.539
that bordered that beach. And one chief said, now that's my sand, the other one,

00:39:51.539 --> 00:39:56.500
said it was his sand. Well, they couldn't come to an agreement, so they weren't willing to sell

00:39:56.500 --> 00:40:02.179
the sand to us. So we were at the stage where we were getting ready to need it in a few days,

00:40:02.179 --> 00:40:05.300
so we could move forward with the extension of the Kingdom Hall.

00:40:06.260 --> 00:40:10.179
